benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Remove tags from account

covered: Valid Deletion: scenarios cover single and multiple tag removal as well as removal of all tags with 204 responses and DB state validation
Boundary/Edge cases: tests cover removal with/without tagDef query params, account with no tags, extra/unexpected query parameters, and empty tagDef array
Header and Authorization: tests cover required header presence, missing header, and unauthorized access (valid user vs invalid/unauthorized)
Input validation: tests cover invalid accountId formats, non-existent account, invalid/malformed tagDef UUIDs
Resilience: service unavailability (5xx) and network failure recovery scenarios
Performance/Concurrency: test for concurrent deletes and large tagDef lists
Regression: tests for mixed valid/invalid tagDef values and backward compatibility with omitted optional headers
No data state: removal on an account with no tags is idempotent and results in 204
gaps: Caching/ETag and Cache-Control headers are not tested
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested
Pagination is not applicable to DELETE; no tests for pagination, if ever relevant
Observability and auditing/logging checks are not covered
recommendations: Add tests to verify and document caching headers for DELETE responses (ETag, Cache-Control).
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper handling under burst traffic and high concurrency.
Consider adding an explicit idempotency test to repeatedly delete the same tag and assert 204 or no errors
Expand test coverage to include observability/auditing checks for delete operations (logs, traces)
